"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Make Agent Integration Skill Resilient to Codebase Drift\n\n## Context\n\nThe agent-integration skill (`.claude/skills/agent-integration/`) contains ~40 hardcoded file paths, enumerated names (event types, runner classes, test files), and inline code examples with method signatures. These already drifted once (PR #498 review caught 10 issues). The root cause is that the skill prompts duplicate information that lives in source code and docs, creating multiple places that must stay in sync.\n\nAdditionally, `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — which the skill prompts reference as authoritative — is itself severely drifted: it lists deleted methods (`HookHandler`, `GetSupportedHooks`, `SupportsHooks`, `GetHookConfigPath`, `ParseHookInput`), says \"19 methods\" when there are 15, and uses the renamed `paths.RepoRoot()` instead of `paths.WorktreeRoot()`.\n\n**Approach: \"Anchor + Discover\"** — Keep stable file paths as entry points, but replace enumerated details with instructions for the AI agent to discover them from source code using its tools (Read, Glob, Grep).\n\n## Scope Decision\n\nThe skill prompts and `agent-guide.md` are tightly coupled — the prompts delegate to the guide as the authoritative source. Fixing only the prompts while the guide remains wrong would leave the agent following incorrect instructions.\n\n**In scope:**\n- `.claude/skills/agent-integration/probe-prompt.md` — replace enumerations with discovery\n- `.claude/skills/agent-integration/e2e-test-prompt.md` — replace enumerations with discovery\n- `.claude/skills/agent-integration/implement-prompt.md` — replace code examples with \"read the interface\" + remove duplicate template code (the guide already has full templates)\n- `.claude/skills/agent-integration/README.md` — minor: make agent listing discoverable\n- `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — fix stale method table, remove deleted interfaces, update `paths.RepoRoot()` → `paths.WorktreeRoot()`, add