ptional capability interfaces\n2. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — Read to find all `EventType` constants (the normalized lifecycle events agents must map to)\n3. `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` — How native hook names are registered and routed\n4. `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — `DispatchLifecycleEvent` handler\n5. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Full implementation guide\n6. `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — Validation criteria\n```\n\n**Reference implementations (lines 21-26):** Replace specific agent listings with discovery.\n```\n**Reference implementations:** Run `Glob(\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\")` to discover all existing agent packages. Pick 1-2 as reference. In each, focus on `lifecycle.go` (ParseHookEvent), `hooks.go` (HookSupport), and `types.go` (hook input structs).\n```\n\n**Compatibility report template — EventType table (lines 110-118):** Replace hardcoded rows with dynamic instruction.\n```\n## Lifecycle Event Mapping\n\nFor each EventType constant found in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go`, create a row:\n\n| Entire EventType | Native Hook | Status | Fields Available |\n|-----------------|-------------|--------|-----------------|\n| (one row per EventType from event.go) | ? | MAPPED/PARTIAL/MISSING | |\n```\n\n**Compatibility report template — Interface feasibility table (lines 122-131):** Replace hardcoded rows with dynamic instruction.\n```\n## Required Interface Feasibility\n\nFor each interface defined in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go`, assess feasibility:\n\n| Interface | Feasible | Complexity | Notes |\n|-----------|----------|------------|-------|\n| Agent (core) | Yes/No/Partial | Low/Med/High | |\n| (one row per optional interface from agent.go) | ... | ... | |\n```\n\n### 3. `e2e-test-prompt.md` — 3 changes\n\n**Step 1 — infrastructure files (lines 15-20):** Keep the 5 structural file names (stable infrastructure), but remove inline enumeration of runner class names.\n```\n3. `cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/agent_runner.go` — `AgentRunner` interface and existing runner implementations. Read the file to discover all current runners and the `NewAgentRunner` factory.\n```\n\n**Step 2 — scenario tests (lines 24-31):** Replace exhaustive file list with glob discovery.\n```\n### Step 2: Read Existing E2E Scenario Tests\n\nRun `Glob(\"cmd/entire/cli/e2e_test/scenario_*_test.go\")` to find all existing scenario tests. Read each to understand the patterns:\n- How scenarios use `TestEnv` and `AgentRunner`\n- How prompts are structured for determinism\n- How assertions validate checkpoints, rewind, etc.\n```\n\n**Step 4 — Create AgentRunner (lines 58-59):** Replace hardcoded constant/switch naming with discovery.\n```\n- Add an agent name constant following the pattern of existing constants in `agent_runner.go`\n- Register in the `NewAgentRunner` factory (search for `func NewAgentRunner` to find it)\n```\n\n### 4. `implement-prompt.md` — 5 changes\n\n**Step 1 — required reading (lines 16-20):** Remove inline content descriptions that enumerate specifics.\n```\n1. `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — Authoritative implementation guide with code templates. Read thoroughly.\n2. `docs/architecture/agent-integration-checklist.md` — Validation criteria for completeness.\n3. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` — Read to find the exact `Agent` interface and all optional interfaces.\n4. `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — Read to find `EventType` constants and shared parsing helpers.\n```\n\n**Step 2 — reference implementation table (lines 25-31):** Replace with discovery.\n```\n### Step 2: Read Reference Implementation\n\nRun `Glob(\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\")` to find all existing agent packages. Pick the closest match based on probe findings — read a few agents' `hooks.go` files to find one with a similar hook mechanism to your target. Read all `*.go` files (skip `*_test.go` on first pass) in the chosen reference.\n```\n\n**Steps 4-9 — TDD cycles (lines 43-221):** Replace inline code examples with \"read the interface + reference\" instructions. The `agent-guide.md` already has comprehensive code templates — the skill prompts should not duplicate them.\n\nFor each TDD step, the pattern becomes:\n```\n**Green**: Create `${file}.go`. Read the relevant interface in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` for exact method signatures. Read the corresponding file in a reference agent (find via `Glob(\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/${file}.go\")`) for the implementation pattern. The `agent-guide.md` has a complete code template if needed.\n```\n\nSpecifically:\n- Step 5 (core agent): Remove the `init()` + struct + method stub code block. Replace with: \"Read Agent interface in agent.go for all methods. Read agent-guide.md Step 3 for the full code template. Use `agent.Register(agent.AgentName(\"$AGENT_SLUG\"), New)` in init().\"\n- Step 6 (lifecycle): Remove the ParseHookEvent code block. Replace with: \"Read HookSupport interface in agent.go. Read agent-guide.md Step 4 for the switch-case pattern.\"\n- Step 7 (hooks): Remove the InstallHooks/UninstallHooks/AreHooksInstalled stubs. Replace with: \"Read HookSupport interface in agent.go for exact signatures. Read agent-guide.md Step 8 for installation pattern.\"\n- Step 8 (transcript): Remove code block. Replace with: \"Read TranscriptAnalyzer interface in agent.go. Read agent-guide.md Transcript Format Guide for JSONL vs JSON patterns.\"\n- Step 9 (optional interfaces): Remove bullet list of interface names. Replace with: \"Read agent.go for all optional interfaces. For each one the probe report marked as feasible, follow the same TDD cycle.\"\n\n**Step 10 — register (lines 223-226):** Already uses discovery (\"Search cmd/entire/cli/ for...\"). Keep as-is.\n\n### 5. `README.md` — 1 change\n\n**Line 50:** Replace hardcoded agent list with discovery pattern.\n```\n- Existing agents: Discover via `Glob(\"cmd/entire/cli/agent/*/\")`\n```\n\n## Files to Modify\n\n| File | Changes | Risk |\n|------|---------|------|\n| `docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` | Fix stale methods, update paths, add caveat | Medium — large file, many code blocks |\n| `.claude/skills/agent-integration/probe-prompt.md` | Replace 4 enumerated sections with discovery | Low |\n| `.claude/skills/agent-integration/e2e-test-prompt.md` | Replace 3 enumerated sections with discovery | Low |\n| `.claude/skills/agent-integration/implement-prompt.md` | Remove 6 code blocks, replace with read-the-source instructions | Medium — largest structural change |\n| `.claude/skills/agent-integration/README.md` | 1-line change | Low |\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `grep -rn 'factoryaidroid\\|FactoryAIDroid' .claude/skills/ docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — should return nothing\n2. `grep -rn 'paths\\.RepoRoot' docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — should return nothing after fix\n3. `grep -rn 'HookHandler\\|GetSupportedHooks' docs/architecture/agent-guide.md` — should return nothing after fix\n4. `grep -rn '19 method' docs/architecture/agent-guide.md .claude/skills/` — should return nothing\n5. Read each modified file end-to-end to verify markdown renders correctly (no unclosed fences)\n6. Verify each skill prompt still has enough structure to guide implementation (not too vague)\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-devenv-cli/e3b9b251-e322-4a6b-b48d-361a9097e77a.jsonl"